episodes.title: Episode #1.1
episodes.plot: In 1977, frustrated FBI hostage negotiator Holden Ford finds an unlikely ally in veteran agent Bill Tench and begins studying a new class of murderer.

episodes.title: Episode #1.2
episodes.plot: Holden interviews the eerily articulate murderer Ed Kemper, but his research provokes negative feedback at the Bureau.

episodes.title: Episode #1.3
episodes.plot: Dr Wendy Carr joins Holden and Tench in their first success, when their insights lead to an arrest.

episodes.title: Episode #1.4
episodes.plot: Bill and Holden consult with Dr Wendy Carr to begin classifying their subjects and they receive surprising news.

episodes.title: Episode #1.5
episodes.plot: Holden and Bill return to a perplexing case in Pennsylvania where a set of clues leading in multiple directions leaves no shortage of suspects.

episodes.title: Episode #1.6
episodes.plot: Wendy considers an offer. Holden and Bill struggle to communicate their findings to the judicial system in the baffling Altoona case.

episodes.title: Episode #1.7
episodes.plot: Wendy takes a career risk to relocate and join the team full time. Holden and Bill find it harder to keep the emotional intensity of work at bay.

episodes.title: Episode #1.8
episodes.plot: Bill and Wendy interview candidates for a fourth member of the team. Holden is intrigued by complaints about a school principal's odd habit.

episodes.title: Episode #1.9
episodes.plot: Holden's methods during a disturbing interview with mass murderer Richard Speck create dissension among the team and kick off an internal FBI probe.

episodes.title: Episode #1.10
episodes.plot: The team cracks under the pressure from an in-house review. Holden's bold style elicits a confession but puts his career, relationships and health at risk.
